I found the codebase in good shape, but two concrete rough edges around the just-landed IDEA-66 dirty-sync work. Let me verify my understanding of the two before writing.

The dirty sync (`/api/git/sync` mode `dirty`) runs the sync **agent** in the background (202) and `handleSync` reloads git status immediately — before the agent finishes. The only thing that re-refreshes afterward is the activity SSE stream, which (a) watches **only** `papercamp/` (`activity.ts:46`), and (b) on the `agent`-type event reloads only agent status, not git status (`stack-panel.tsx:94-97`). So when a merged branch's tree equals main, the agent's `git checkout main` touches no `papercamp/` file → no `changed` event → the Commit card keeps its old branch stamp and the "Branch merged — sync to main" button until a manual refresh.

And `DIRTY_SYNC_PROMPT` (`routes/git.ts:8-16`) stashes-or-commits, checks out main, then ff-merges `origin/main` — but never pops the stash or moves the commit onto main, so genuinely uncommitted work lands on the old branch/stash, not main, despite the `commit-section.tsx:429` "carried, not lost" comment.

Both are new and not in the existing ideas/suggestions. Appending them.
