Appended two suggestions to `papercamp/suggestions.md`, both follow-ups to the freshly-landed IDEA-66 dirty-sync work:

1. **Stale git status after background sync** — the sync agent runs async and the only post-completion refresh comes via the SSE stream, which watches only `papercamp/` and reloads just agent status on the `agent` event. When a merged branch's tree equals main, the checkout fires no `changed` event, so the Commit card keeps showing the old branch stamp and the "Branch merged — sync to main" button until a manual refresh.

2. **Dirty-sync disposition of uncommitted work** — `DIRTY_SYNC_PROMPT` stashes-or-commits, checks out main, ff-merges, but never pops the stash or lands the commit on main, so genuinely uncommitted changes end up stranded off main despite the "carried, not lost" comment.

I left everything else untouched — the rest of the server/CLI surface I read (route error handling is uniformly wrapped by the top-level catch in `api.ts:124`, promote/dismiss endpoints, polling) looked sound and I didn't want to force additional items.
